The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Greenhorn had a population of 247. The population density was {{convert|36.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Greenhorn was 211 (85.4%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 7 (2.8%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 2 (0.8%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 9 (3.6%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 18 (7.3%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 22 persons (8.9%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Greenhorn CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0631029 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 108 households, out of which 18 (16.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 47 (43.5%) were married-couple households, 7 (6.5%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 16 (14.8%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 38 (35.2%) had a male householder with no partner present. 47 households (43.5%) were one person, and 13 (12.0%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.29.<ref name=DP1/> There were 53 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (49.1% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Greenhorn CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0631029 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 54 people (21.9%) under the age of 18, 7 people (2.8%) aged 18 to 24, 62 people (25.1%) aged 25 to 44, 49 people (19.8%) aged 45 to 64, and 75 people (30.4%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 46.5{{nbsp}}years.    For every 100 females, there were 120.5 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 140 housing units at an average density of {{convert|20.9|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 108 (77.1%) were occupied. Of these, 66 (61.1%) were owner-occupied, and 42 (38.9%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
At the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]] Greenhorn had a population of 236. The population density was {{convert|35.2|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Greenhorn was 213 (90.3%) White, 1 (0.4%) African American, 7 (3.0%) Native American, 2 (0.8%) Asian, 0 (0.0%) Pacific Islander, 6 (2.5%) from other races, and 7 (3.0%) from two or more races.  Hispanic or Latino of any race were 22 people (9.3%).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0631029|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715025240/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0631029|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Greenhorn CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households, no one lived in non-institutionalized group quarters and no one was institutionalized.

There were 106 households, 23 (21.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 56 (52.8%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 4 (3.8%) had a female householder with no husband present, 4 (3.8%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 7 (6.6%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 1 (0.9%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 33 households (31.1%) were one person and 9 (8.5%) had someone living alone who was 65 or older. The average household size was 2.23.  There were 64 families (60.4% of households); the average family size was 2.81.

The age distribution was 43 people (18.2%) under the age of 18, 15 people (6.4%) aged 18 to 24, 47 people (19.9%) aged 25 to 44, 88 people (37.3%) aged 45 to 64, and 43 people (18.2%) who were 65 or older.  The median age was 46.9 years. For every 100 females, there were 96.7 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 103.2 males.

There were 140 housing units at an average density of 20.9 per square mile, of the occupied units 95 (89.6%) were owner-occupied and 11 (10.4%) were rented. The homeowner vacancy rate was 6.9%; the rental vacancy rate was 8.3%.  211 people (89.4% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 25 people (10.6%) lived in rental housing units.

